dismissalText.long: c Sarfaraz Ahmed b Umar Gul
dismissalText.commentary: Yuvraj Singh c Sarfaraz Ahmed b Umar Gul 50 (62b 3x4 1x6 120m) SR: 80.64

dismissalComment.html: short one banged in, it's quick, Yuvraj goes for the pull and is a touch late. There's a spontaneous and loud appeal from behind the stumps and in front. The umpire, Suresh Shastri, thinks about it for a second and gives it in the bowler's favour. Yuvraj can't believe the call and stands rooted to his crease. This could be interesting. It looks like he's suggesting to the umpire that it came off shoulder. Either way, he has to walk off, and India's chances have taken a serious blow with the fall of that wicket

dismissalText.commentary: Irfan Pathan b Sohail Tanvir 43 (39b 4x4 1x6 61m) SR: 110.25

commentTextItems.html: quick yorker on the off stump. Pathan tries to give himself room and hit through the off. He misses and the off stump is pegged back. That is the end of the Indian innings and this match.

commentPostTextItems.html: With that Pakistan have won this game by 31 runs and eked out a consolation win. India win the series 3-2.

Shoaib Malik top scored with 89, picked up some wickets and will probably walk away with the Man of the Match and steal the headlines, but it was Sohail Tanveer who did the damage in the top half. He bowled exceptionally well to some of India's most destructive batsmen and dismissed them early.
Stay with us and we'll bring you details from the post-match presentaions.
First the match officials receive their medallions for the series. The match referee and the umpires come on and get their souvenirs.

"It was good for us, especially before the Test series," says Shoaib Malik who was named Man of the Match. "Credit goes to the team for the way they put in effort. My form is also alright. I've come good at the right time."
The Indian team comes across to receive medallions for winning this series. The coaching and support staff come up first. The players follow soon after.
After all the medals are distributed it's time for the Man of the Series and it's Yuvraj Singh for his allround performance in the series.

"Everyone played well when it was required. There's scope for improvement in the fielding, but we're working hard," says Mahendra Singh Dhoni. "We lost wickets early on and then had to catch up. The required rate kept mounting and it was the initial wickets that made it really hard."

With that we come to the end of coverage of this game. Thank you very much for following the ODIs on Cricinfo. Do stay with us for the Tests and all the other live cricket we have. For the moment this is Anand Vasu, saying cheers, and signing off.
